		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Fx3 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">bunnyboy wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">There's 8KB of CHR RAM, MMC1 can do CHR banking in 4KB chunks, so that 2 banks.  RAM vs ROM doesn't make any difference for address lines.</div><br />Two banks... so I suppose the value C000 is ANDed with 1..?</div>
<br />Yes, on carts with 8 KiB of CHR (be it ROM or RAM), the bank number is in effect ANDed with 1.

		

